						<summary>

						<p>On the capital of a pillar, proper left in the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>11th-12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It contains praises of two brothers, Guḍayyaseṭṭi and KanṇIseṭṭi and seems to record a gift of one <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> of land out of the 26 <hi rend="italic">mattars</hi> to god Āha[va]mallēśvara.</p>						

						<p>The characters belong to about 11th-12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
